386→                        <div id="content">Let $n\geq 1$ and define $L_n$ to be the least common multiple of $\{1,\ldots,n\}$ and $a_n$ by\[\sum_{1\leq k\leq n}\frac{1}{k}=\frac{a_n}{L_n}.\]Is it true that $(a_n,L_n)=1$ and $(a_n,L_n)&#62;1$ both occur for infinitely many $n$?</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/291">#291</a>: <a href="#cite-ErGr80-291" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('ErGr80','291'); return false;">[ErGr80,p.34]</a></div>
